<br>
To all those who participated, you made yesterday's Open Raid an event to remember.  The cooperation, teamwork, patience, and enthusiasm you displayed was truly remarkable and though many of you have congratulated me on the raid, I think you are the ones that deserve the congratulations for yesterday's event.<br>
<br>
As for loot (off the top of my head):<br>
<br>
Korhil (finally) took one more step towards completing his epic and won the roll for the Torn Book.  Imagine the fights he will have with his wife over this.<br>
<br>
Medite (whose recent luck on rolls is nothing less than astounding) won the roll on the Cloak of Flames.  Although I hated to win the roll, all you melees can take comfort in the fact that I will not be rollling on any other Cloaks on any other Open Naggy Raids that I lead (I still have a few left in me yet).<br>
<br>
Higgin won the Heirophant's Crook and looks really mean now.<br>
<br>
Suometar won the Mithril Torque and was again someone who works under the radar to make my job sooo much easier (consider this a post in the KUDOS section -- let me know when you want me to do that combine).<br>
<br>
Abraxasl won Mithril Vampbraces on his first dragon raid.  Welcome to the Open Raid Community...just don't expect any loot for the next ten raids.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   It was great to have you there.<br>
<br>
Ukko won a Crystal of some sort.  He knows what its for and it seemed to make him chuckle.<br>
<br>
Legalisa won the Bladestopper; maybe we won't have to say RANGA DOWN!  on future raids.<br>
<br>
Borblefoot won a druid bauble of some sort.<br>
<br>
SPECIAL KUDOS<br>
<br>
I could go on and on, but this is the short list:<br>
<br>
To Freaknik the wonder puller.  On next week's Naggy raid, the WR bag will be a monk only roll in honor of your many deaths and contributions to the Open Raid Community.<br>
<br>
To Voskor, you are one mean Lizard.  You rush in week after week and never bat an eye.....on the other hand, I don't think that Iksar have eyelids so this might have something to do with it.  From one MA to another, you know your stuff and it's a pleasure to watch you work.  I think this is where I say &quot;mad props?&quot;<br>
<br>
To Moxxi (aka The Backstop), great offtanking.  I knew from the moment I saw you at work in Kael that no Giant was safe with you around.<br>
<br>
To Emosewa (Uber Buffer) and Lutra, thank you for feeding me a great idea at a time when it looked like we would really need it.  You taught this old dog a new trick. <br>
<br>
To Mariuss (aka The Summoner) you do a thankless job but that extra fire resist we all have courtesy of you keeps us all alive.  Thank You!<br>
<br>
To Bobok, Ukko, and Abbraxas -- you make us all look sooo good.  We wouldn't make it past the Sonic Bats without you.<br>
<br>
To Merck (aka the Crack Dealer), you hasted and claritied and GRMd us to victory, my friend.  I'm glad you stayed out of the lava and made it to the Druid ring!  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
To Borblefoot, your junk buffs and instructions in the buff phase helps speed that process along.  Your transportation means that these things start on time.  Thanks!<br>
<br>
To Queth, for reminding me (and others) of the importance of savoring the moment and taking the time to take a few screenshots of Lord Nagafen in his more....relaxed state before looting the corpse.  You classed up the joint.<br>
<br>
I could go on like this for awhile.  Instead, I'll just say well done and I hope to see you again next Sunday.<br>
<br>
Medite Marconus<br>
